  "texts": [
    "One of the primary limitations of SK-Tuning is the potential increase in inference or training time.",
    "Since it utilizes the pre-trained LLM twice during the forward pass: once to obtain semantic information from the prompt or prefix and again for processing the input data to get output.",
    "This dual usage of the LLM can lead to longer training and inference time.",
    "SK-Tuning relies heavily on the quality and capabilities of the underlying pretrained LLM.",
    "The success of prompt or prefix text tuning is linked to the zero-shot capabilities of the LLM."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}